ers%2C%20such%20as%20auto-parts%20makers%2C%20which%20get%20as%20much%20as%20one-third%20of%20their%20revenue%20from%20these%20three%20companies%2C%20are%20also%20expected%20to%20see%20major%20drops%20in%20earnings%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBloomberg%20reported%20a%20UAW%20strike%20against%20any%20of%20the%20automakers%20could%20have%20a%20similar%20impact%20on%20the%20auto%20industry%20as%20the%20six-week%202019%20GM%20strike%2C%20which%20cost%20GM%20about%20%242.9%20billion%20and%20hurt%20auto-parts%20makers%20and%20steel%20producers.%20Steel%20production%20is%20also%20expected%20to%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UAW%20has%20rejected%20offers%20from%20the%20three%20companies%2C%20which%20included%20pay%20raises%20between%2014.5%25%20and%2016%25%20for%20most%20union%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strike%20could%20seep%20into%20politics%20as%20campaigning%20picks%20up%20for%20the%202024%20presidential%20election.%20Key%20swing%20states%20such%20as%20Michigan%20and%20Wisconsin%20would%20likely%20take%20large%20economic%20hits%20from%20the%20strike%2C%20which%20could%20hurt%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20chances%20of%20winning%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECar%20prices%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FCUUR0000SETA01%230%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeen%20leveling%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20manufacturers%20have%20built%20up%20inventories%20since%20the%20big%20price%20spikes%20at%20the%20height%20of%20pandemic%20supply-chain%20woes.%20But%20a%20strike%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuaw-strike-high-prices-low-inventory-car-deals-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecut%20into%20those%20inventories%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20leading%20to%20renewed%20price%20hikes%20and%20a%20new%20round%20of%20customer%20anxiety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F09%2F11%2Fbusiness%2Fautomakers-strike-negotiations-uaw%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esaid%20last%20week%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20he%20expected%20the%20strike%20to%20be%20avoided%2C%20though%20he%20lacks%20the%20legal%20authority%20to%20order%20both%20sides%20to%20continue%20working.%20Deputy%20Treasury%20Secretary%20Wally%20Adeyemo%20confirmed%20to%20CNBC%20Monday%20that%20the%20Biden%20administration%20anticipated%20a%20deal%20between%20UAW%20and%20automakers%20after%20appointing%20top%20officials%20to%20help%20facilitate%20talks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UAW%2C%20which%20has%20historically%20supported%20Democrats%2C%20has%20not%20endorsed%20Biden's%20reelection%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20our%20strike%20can%20reaffirm%20to%20%5BBiden%5D%20of%20where%20the%20working-class%20people%20in%20this%20country%20stand%20and%2C%20you%20know%2C%20it's%20time%20for%20politicians%20in%20this%20country%20to%20pick%20a%20side%2C%26quot%3B%20Fain%20said%20during%20CNBC's%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2Flast-call%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELast%20Call%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20with%20Brian%20Sullivan.%20%26quot%3BEither%20you%20stand%20for%20a%20billionaire%20class%20where%20everybody%20else%20gets%20left%20behind%2C%20or%20you%20stand%20for%20the%20working%20class%2C%20the%20working-class%20people%20vote.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauto-industry-uaw-strike-effects-inflation-michigan-recession-biden-election-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694471605000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64fb3e2da39a1b00190bd21f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauto-industry-uaw-strike-effects-inflation-michigan-recession-biden-election-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20UAW%20strike%20would%20affect%20more%20than%20the%20auto%20industry%3A%20Inflation%20could%20rise%2C%20Michig