20Ucko%20argues%20that%20as%20US%20special-operations%20forces%20shift%20from%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-socom-learned-in-afghanistan-means-for-future-fights-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwo%20decades%20of%20mostly%20low-intensity%20fighting%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20terrorist%20groups%20and%20insurgents%2C%20US%20leaders%20need%20to%20focus%20on%20using%20those%20forces%20for%20missions%20within%20their%20competencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUcko%20writes%20that%20strategic%20competition%20requires%20more%20than%20violence%20and%20preparation%20for%20combat%20%E2%80%94%20at%20which%20commandos%20excel%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20political%20warfare%20is%20also%20a%20key%20element%2C%20making%20four%20main%20arguments%20about%20how%20to%20get%20the%20most%20out%20of%20special-operations%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20the%20US%20special-operations%20community%20should%20consolidate%20its%20core%20strengths%2C%20particularly%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-bureaucratic-change-sign-of-military-return-to-irregular-warfare-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eirregular%20warfare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20relevant%26quot%3B%20to%20strategic%20competition%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20outside%20of%20tasks%20related%20to%20irregular%20warfare%2C%20restraint%20is%20warranted%20because%20of%20%26quot%3Binevitable%20limits%20on%20SOF's%20bandwidth%2C%20the%20trade-offs%20inherent%20to%20adding%20more%20to%20an%20already%20full%20plate%2C%20and%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20competition%2C%20which%20in%20most%20respects%20remains%20a%20non-military%20phenomenon.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Air%20Force%20Special%20Tactics%20CV-22B%20Osprey%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ff23a13d39230019781b62%3Fform