ill%20still%20fall%20short%20of%20its%20war%20needs.%20It%20also%20pales%20in%20comparison%20to%20what%20Russia's%20been%20using%20up.%20Just%20last%20week%2C%20one%20Western%20official%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-66771568%5C%22%3Etold%20the%20BBC%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20estimates%20suggested%20Russia%20fired%20between%2010%20million%20and%2011%20million%20rounds%20in%20Ukraine%20last%20year%20after%20its%20initial%20full-scale%20invasion.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20clear%20need%20for%20firepower%20and%20a%20dwindling%20group%20of%20allies%20to%20get%20it%20from%2C%20Russia%20is%20turning%20to%20North%20Korea.%20But%20while%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-desperation-in-ukraine-closer-ties-with-iran-north-korea-2022-11%5C%22%3Emove%20seems%20frantic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20also%20calculated.%20North%20Korea%20makes%20headlines%20for%20its%20nuclear%20weapons%20program%2C%20but%20the%20dictatorship%20also%20has%20a%20threatening%20artillery%20presence%20that%20could%20give%20Russia%20the%20stopgap%20it%20needs%20to%20keep%20pounding%20away%20at%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222362%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Korean%20People's%20Army%20(KPA)%20artillery%20troops%20conduct%20a%20live%20firing%20exercise.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ff47684b33390019f09254%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221185%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKorean%20People's%20Army%20(KPA)%20artillery%20troops%20conduct%20a%20live%20firing%20exercise.%3Cp%3EKCNA%2FREUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202020%2C%20think%20tank%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rand.org%2Fpubs%2Fresearch_reports%2FRRA619-1.html%5C%22%3ERand%20Corp%20assessed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20North%20Korea%20maintains%20about%206%2C000%20deadly%20artillery%20systems%20within%20range%20of%20major%20South%20Korean%20population%20centers%2C%20including%20Seoul.%20