%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-data-shows-the-world-is-running-out-of-water-2015-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEarth%20can%20naturally%20replenish%20it%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffissure-arizona-largest-kind-crack-earth-surface-desert-two-miles-long-2017-1%5C%22%3Etoo%20much%20groundwater%20gets%20pumped%3C%2Fa%3E%20up%20from%20the%20natural%20aquifers%20below%20the%20surface%2C%20it%20causes%20the%20land%20to%20sag%20and%20create%20these%20cracks%2C%20Joseph%20Cook%2C%20who%20researches%20Earth%20fissures%20at%20the%20Arizona%20Geological%20Survey%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fissures%20%26quot%3Bare%20not%20a%20naturally%20occurring%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20Cook%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20something%20we've%20caused%20to%20form.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22785%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Crack%20in%20ground%20in%20California%20from%20groundwater%20depletion.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64fd0e18a39a1b00190c9b49%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22559%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20giant%20fissure%20in%20the%20Mojave%20Desert%20in%20California%20from%20groundwater%20pumping%20near%20Lucerne%20Lake.%3Cp%3EUSGS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cracks%20are%20signs%20of%20tension%20in%20the%20Earth%2C%20Cook%20said.%20They%20rim%20large%20flat%20areas%20of%20ground%20that%20sunk%20when%20it%20lost%20the%20support%20of%20groundwater.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFissures%20commonly%20occur%20in%20the%20basins%20between%20mountains%20and%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fazgs.arizona.edu%2Fcenter-natural-hazards%2Fearth-fissures-subsidence-karst-arizona%3Fpage%3D1%5C%22%3Edamage%3C%2Fa%3E%20homes%2C%20roads%2C%20canals%2C%20and%20dams%20as%20well%20as%20threaten%20property%20values%2C%20livestock%2C%20and%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22near%20Sulphur%20Hills%20(southeast%20of%20Willcox%20Playa)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f8ed8556f5190019fc853c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20fissure%20opened%20up%20beneath%20the%20road%20near%20Sulphur%20Hills.%3Cp%3EJoseph%20Cook%2FAZGS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EArizona%20has%20known%20about%20this%20problem%20for%20a%20long%20time%20and%20has%20been%20monitoring%20it%20since%20at%20least%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnew.azwater.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FHJ_LandSubsidenceandEarthFissuresinArizona.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2002%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20169%20miles%20of%20fissures%20currently%20charted%20by%20the%20Arizona%20Geological%20Survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Picacho%20Basin%2C%20AZ%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f8ed9d56f5190019fc8553%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20drone%20view%20of%20a%20fissure%20over%20Picacho%20Basin%2C%20Arizona.%3Cp%3EBrian%20Gootee%2F%20AZGS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20national%20crisis%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2023%2F08%2F28%2Fclimate%2Fgroundwater-drying-climate-change.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20investigation%20noted%20that%20the%20fissures%20are%20evidence%20of%20a%20national%20crisis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Times%20investigated%20water%20levels%20at%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20sites%20across%20the%20US.%20It%20reported%20that%20the%20aquifers%2C%20which%20supply%20about%2090%25%20of%20US%20water%20systems%2C%20are%20being%20depleted%20so%20severely%20they%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20recover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222846%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Picacho%20Basin%2C%20AZ%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f8eda656f5190019fc8563%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222135%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20fissures%20can%20stretch%20for%20over%20a%20mile.%3Cp%3EBrian%20Conway%2FAZGS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20half%20of%20the%20monitored%20sites%20have%20%26quot%3Bdeclined%20significantly%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20past%2040%20years.%20And%20four%20out%20of%20every%2010%20sites%20hit%20%26quot%3Ball-time%20lows%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20past%20decade%20as%20American%20groundwater%20pumping%20outpaces%20water%20replenishment%2C%20per%20the%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAquifers%20could%20take%20centuries%20or%20even%20thousands%20of%20years%20to%20recover%20if%20they%20can%20recover%20at%20all%2C%20the%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20sites%20in%20Arizona%20are%20already%20beyond%20saving%2C%20according%20to%20Cook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20ground%20fissure%20splits%20the%20desert%20ground%20heading%20towards%20a%20distant%20mountain%20range%2C%20with%20a%20surveyor%20standing%20on%20the%20edge%20in%20the%20distance.%20near%20Sulphur%20Hills%20(southeast%20of%20Willcox%20Playa%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f9cec956f5190019fcd404%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDeep%20groundwater%20reserves%20can%20take%20thousands%20of%20years%20to%20replenish.%3Cp%3EJoesph%20Cook%2FAZGS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20water%20use%20has%20been%20so%20consistent%20and%20extreme%20that%20it%20hasn't%20allowed%20enough%20time%20for%20rainwater%20to%20replenish%20underground%20aquifers%2C%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBasically%2C%20some%20of%20these%20basins%20in%20Arizona%20are%20so%20far%20beyond%20that%20point%20that%20it's%20never%20going%20to%20bounce%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20Cook%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EClimate%20change%20makes%20it%20worse%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclimate-change-alter-human-life-un-ipcc-report-2022-2%5C%22%3Eclimate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20added%20into%20the%20mix%2C%20the%20makings%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bcrisis%26quot%3B%20are%20well%20underway%2C%20University%20of%20Tulsa%20law%20professor%20and%20water%20expert%20Warigia%20Bowman%20told%20the%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20global%20temperatures%20rise%2C%20rivers%20shrink%2C%20forcing%20farmers%20to%20rely%20even%20more%20on%20groundwater%20reserves%20for%20freshwater%2C%20per%20the%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Colorado%20River%2C%20which%20supplies%20freshwater%20for%20farmers%20across%20the%20Southwest%20including%20Arizona%2C%20has%20already%20declined%20by%20nearly%2020%25%20since%202000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20dead%20fish%20in%20dried%20up%20Queens%20Reservoir.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64fd28b03d3923001977aa07%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22740%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELast%20year%2C%20an%20emergency%20public%20fish%20salvage%20was%20issued%20for%20Queens%20Reservoir%20when%20drought%20conditions%20dried%20up%20the%20reservoir%20in%20Eads%2C%20Colorado.%20This%20fish%20didn't%20make%20it.%3Cp%3ERJ%20Sangosti%2FMediaNews%20Group%2FThe%20Denver%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%20%2F%20Contributor%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20global%20temperatures%20in%20the%20Colorado%20River%20Basin%20rise%20another%202-5%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%20by%202050%2C%20as%20predicted%2C%20it%20could%20reduce%20river%20flow%20by%2010%25%20to%2040%25%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.climaterealityproject.org%2Fblog%2Fwater-and-us-southwest%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Climate%20Reality%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20did%20it%20get%20this%20bad%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20main%20issues%20in%20addressing%20over-pumping%20is%20the%20lack%20of%20regulation%20that%20exists%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20government%20has%20almost%20no%20regulations%20against%20groundwater%20pumping%2C%20and%20individual%20states%20have%20weak%2C%20variable%20rules%20from%20region%20to%20region%2C%20per%20the%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20ground%20fissure%20heads%20towards%20the%20mountain%20ranges%20near%20Sulphur%20Hills%20(southeast%20of%20Willcox%20Playa)%20on%20a%20bright%20desert%20day.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f8edaa8a7840001961b456%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGiant%20cracks%20in%20Arizona%20are%20due%20to%20excessive%20groundwater%20depletion.%3Cp%3EJoseph%20Cook%2FAZGS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EArizona%20is%20no%20exception.%20For%20most%20of%20its%20history%2C%20groundwater%20has%20been%20unregulated%20in%20much%20of%20the%20state%2C%20operating%20on%20a%20first%20come%20first%20serve%20basis%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorymaps.arcgis.com%2Fstories%2F116b7d04752649dfa8d81df3a3c3556f%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Audubon%20Society%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20no%20limit%20on%20how%20much%20groundwater%20can%20be%20used%2C%20and%20people%20can%20simply%20drain%20the%20groundwater%20until%20it%20runs%20out%2C%20Cook%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222736%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Picacho%20Basin%2C%20AZ%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f9ced756f5190019fcd40c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222057%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20deep%20fissure%20near%20Pica