is%20fan%20ever%20since%20she%20was%20in%20her%20mother's%20womb.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fjawan-actress-lehar-khan-says-shah-rukh-khan-looked-after-his-girls-and-gave-the-warmest-hugs%2Farticleshow%2F103583117.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22G20%3A%20Modi%20Plays%20an%20Old%20Game%2C%20Walking%20in%20the%20Footsteps%20of%20Nehru%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F08123806%2FUntitled-design.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%2080-year-old%20President%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20it%20was%20a%20hectic%20weekend.%20After%20a%20bilateral%20meeting%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20participation%20in%20the%20proceedings%20of%20the%20G20%20Summit%2C%20he%20landed%20in%20Hanoi%20and%20was%20ready%20for%20a%2020-minute%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D-k9h_iUzz2A%5C%22%3Einteraction%20with%20the%20media%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Surprisingly%20focused%20and%20pointed%20in%20his%20remarks%20and%20replies%2C%20Biden%20spoke%20on%20a%20range%20of%20issues%2C%20including%20American%20concerns%20about%20human%20rights%20and%20civil%20liberties%20in%20India%2C%20Xi%20Jinping%E2%80%99s%20absence%20at%20the%20G20%20summit%2C%20US-China%20relations%2C%20the%20state%20of%20the%20Chinese%20economy%20and%20so%20on.%20However%2C%20put%20it%20down%20to%20his%20age%2C%20or%20just%20a%20Freudian%20Slip%2C%20he%20kept%20referring%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98Global%20South%E2%80%99%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Third%20World%E2%80%99.%20Therein%20lies%20a%20tale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Ffive-keys-takeaways-from-the-g20-summit-in-delhi%5C%22%3EFive%20Keys%20Takeaways%20From%20the%20G20%20Summit%20in%20Delhi%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Group%20of%20Seven%20(G7)%20rich%20industrial%20economies%20continue%20to%20view%20the%20Global%20South%20as%20the%20Third%20World%2C%20even%20if%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20keeps%20reminding%20the%20world%20that%20India%20will%20soon%20be%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20third%20largest%20economy.%20Yes%2C%20India%20has%20landed%20a%20spacecraft%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20and%20has%20done%20much%20that%20we%20can%20genuinely%20be%20proud%20of%2C%20but%20then%20India%20was%20a%20nuclear%20and%20space%20power%20even%20when%20it%20was%20poorer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20balancing%20act%20of%20Indian%20diplomacy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20New%20Delhi%20Summit%20was%20a%20success%2C%20and%20it%20was%2C%20this%20was%20not%20on%20account%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20emergence%20as%20a%20global%20%E2%80%98superpower%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20some%20in%20the%20ruling%20party%20have%20been%20claiming%2C%20but%20on%20account%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20Indian%20diplomacy%20used%20two%20tried%20and%20tested%20cards%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20diplomatic%20playbook%20that%20had%20worked%20in%20the%20past%20and%20that%20have%20worked%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fg20-summit-indonesia-key-takeaways-8913395%2F%5C%22%3EG20%20Summit%20in%20Bali%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Indonesia%2C%20in%20November%202022%2C%20the%20United%20States%20and%20the%20European%20Union%20succeeded%20in%20cornering%20Russia%20and%20admonishing%20its%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20Russia%20protested%20that%20since%20its%20inception%20the%20G20%20had%20focused%20only%20on%20global%20economic%20issues%2C%20steering%20clear%20of%20geopolitics%20and%20security-related%20issues.%20This%20plea%2C%20voiced%20also%20by%20China%2C%20was%20rejected%20and%20a%20formulation%20critical%20of%20Russia%20was%20introduced.%20Worse%2C%20from%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20point%20of%20view%2C%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20was%20allowed%20to%20address%20the%20Bali%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Modi%20was%20well%20aware%20that%20India%20could%20ill%20afford%20to%20embarrass%20Russia%20in%20this%20manner.%20Unlike%20Indonesia%2C%20India%20has%20deep%20and%20long-standing%20relations%20with%20Russia%20and%20these%20still%20matter.%20While%20there%20were%20some%20in%20India%20who%20felt%20the%20G20%20should%20have%20a%20wider%20scope%20beyond%20economics%20and%20should%20discuss%20security-related%20issues%2C%20including%20terrorism%2C%20given%20that%20India%20was%20not%20a%20member%20of%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20but%20was%20a%20founding%20member%20of%20G20%2C%20there%20were%20others%20who%20did%20not%20quite%20go%20along%20with%20this%20view.%20Returning%20home%20from%20Indonesia%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20began%20consulting%20various%20individuals%2C%20apart%20from%20his%20own%20colleagues%20and%20came%20to%20the%20view%20that%20if%20the%20New%20Delhi%20summit%20has%20to%20avoid%20the%20pitfall%20of%20Big%20Power%20rivalry%2C%20then%20India%20must%20play%20a%20decisive%20role%20in%20setting%20the%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20chose%20to%20make%20it%20clear%20that%20it%20would%20continue%20to%20balance%20its%20relations%20between%20the%20G7%20and%20Russia.%20The%20message%20was%20clearly%20communicated%20to%20all%20G7%20heads%20of%20government.%20While%20Modi%20was%20willing%20to%20rap%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20by%20declaring%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20is%20no%20era%20of%20war%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20ignored%20G7%20economic%20sanctions%20and%20continued%20to%20buy%20and%20process%20Russian%20crude%20oil.%20Even%20as%20he%20kept%20Russian%20leadership%20happy%2C%20Modi%20flew%20into%20the%20United%20States%20and%20France%2C%20signed%20major%20defence%20deals%2C%20and%20paid%20for%20G7%20friendship.%20In%20doing%20all%20this%2C%20Modi%20was%20using%20an%20old%20Nehru-Indira%20diplomatic%20card.%20It%20was%20easier%20for%20him%20to%20play%20this%20card%20because%20in%202023%20India%20had%20more%20diplomatic%20space%20in%20world%20affairs%20than%20was%20the%20case%2C%20at%20least%20in%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%E2%80%99s%20second%20card%20was%20pure%20Nehruvian.%20He%20decided%20to%20revive%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98voice%E2%80%99%20for%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20focusing%20on%20developmental%20challenges%20and%20championing%20the%20entry%20of%20Africa%20into%20the%20G20.%20It%20used%20to%20be%20called%20Afro-Asian%20Solidarity%20in%20the%201950s.%20A%20poorer%20%E2%80%98Old%20India%E2%80%99%20was%20the%20voice%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Third%20World%E2%80%99.%20A%20richer%20%E2%80%98New%20India%E2%80%99%20is%20now%20the%20%E2%80%98Voice%20of%20the%20Global%20South%E2%80%99.%20The%20Nehru%20jacket%20was%20re-stitched%2C%20in%20many%20colours%20and%20sold%20as%20the%20Modi%20jacket.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F09131958%2FF5j7GbpbAAA7TEp.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F09131958%2FF5j7GbpbAAA7TEp.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F09131958%2FF5j7GbpbAAA7TEp-300x240.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F09131958%2FF5j7GbpbAAA7TEp-1024x819.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-672274%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20hugs%20the%20current%20chair%20of%20the%20African%20Union%2C%20President%20of%20Comoros%20Azali%20Assoumani.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40MEAIndia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20month%20of%20the%20Bali%20Summit%2C%20Modi%20decided%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20%E2%80%98Global%20South%E2%80%99.%20By%20Christmas%20Day%20in%202022%2C%20the%20External%20Affairs%20Ministry%20was%20busy%20contacting%20125%20countries%20around%20the%20world%2C%20inviting%20them%20to%20join%20a%20virtual%20summit%20to%20be%20chaired%20by%20Modi.%20In%20the%20months%20after%20the%20%E2%80%98Voice%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20Summit%E2%80%99%2C%20held%20virtually%20on%20January%2012-13%2C%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20travelled%20extensively%20around%20Africa%2C%20Latin%20America%2C%20and%20Eastern%20Europe.%20From%20then%2C%20the%20G20%20agenda%20began%20to%20focus%20on%20issues%20of%20interest%20to%20the%20developing%20countries.%20Consider%20the%20countries%20that%20Modi%20directly%20courted%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20Delhi%20Summit.%20Egypt%20as%20chief%20guest%20at%20the%20Republic%20Day%20parade%20in%20January%202023.%20A%20quick%20visit%20to%20Indonesia%20a%20day%20before%20the%20Delhi%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20Egypt%2C%20and%20Indonesia%20were%20among%20the%20original%20architects%20of%20%E2%80%98third%20world%20solidarity%E2%80%99.%20The%20Delhi%20Declaration%20reinforced%20the%20text%20on%20all%20issues%20of%20interest%20to%20the%20developing%20world%2C%20ranging%20from%20debt%20relief%20to%20less%20developed%20economies%2C%20to%20climate%20and%20pandemic-related%20financial%20support%2C%20reform%20of%20multilateral%20financial%20institutions%20and%20multilateral%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20other%20significant%20development%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20Delhi%20Summit%20also%20contributed%20to%20its%20success.%20This%20was%20the%20expansion%20of%20BRICS%20made%20possible%20by%20China%E2%80%99s%20leadership.%20Till%20that%20point%2C%20the%20G7%20were%20circling%20their%20wagons%20and%20seeking%20to%20retain%20control%20over%20the%20G20.%20After%20all%2C%20it%20was%20the%20G7%20that%20created%20the%20G20.%20The%20only%20substantial%20contribution%20of%20the%20G20%20till%20last%20year%20was%20what%20it%20managed%20to%20do%20in%202008-09%20to%20salvage%20the%20trans-Atlantic%20economies.%20The%20expansion%20of%20BRICS%20rang%20alarm%20bells%20in%20G7%20capitals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fg20-turns-g21-as-african-union-becomes-a-permanent-member%5C%22%3EG20%20Turns%20G21%20as%20African%20Union%20Becomes%20a%20Permanent%20Member%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIntellectual%20foot%20soldiers%20of%20the%20West%20were%20quick%20to%20despatch%20columns%20pooh-pooing%20BRICS%20expansion.%20BRICS%20is%20irrelevant%2C%20bigger%20BRICS%20is%20even%20more%20irrelevant%20was%20the%20verdict.%20India%20should%20quit%20Brics%2C%20Western%20analysts%20wrote%2C%20since%20China%20has%20come%20to%20dominate%20it.%20China%20always%20dominated%20Brics.%20The%20point%20is%20India%20saw%20some%20value%20in%20keeping%20one%20foot%20in%20that%20camp%20even%20as%20it%20placed%20another%20foot%20firmly%20in%20the%20Western%20camp.%20Finally%2C%20as%20some%20European%20diplomats%20confessed%20over%20the%20weekend%2C%20if%20the%20Delhi%20summit%20had%20failed%2C%20there%20was%20the%20fear%20that%20G20%20would%20become%20unmanageable%20with%20the%20G7%20and%20BRICS%20pulling%20it%20in%20different%20directions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20in%20India%20were%20angry%20with%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20stay%20away%20from%20the%20Delhi%20Summit%2C%20Modi%20would%20know%20that%20it%20was%20in%20fact%20the%20G7%E2%80%99s%20growing%20concern%20about%20China%E2%80%99s%20influence%20that%20enabled%20him%20to%20secure%20a%20G20%20consensus%20on%20the%20Delhi%20Declaration.%20Xi%E2%80%99s%20absence%20may%20well%20have%20helped%20strengthen%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20hands%20in%20his%20last-minute%20negotiations%20for%20a%20consensual%20declaration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20Modi%20kept%20the%20US%20and%20Europe%20happy%20with%20the%20many%20deals%20he%20has%20been%20able%20to%20strike%2C%20especially%20in%20defence%3B%20he%20has%20kept%20Russia%20happy%2C%20so%20much%20so%20that%20he%20was%20willing%20to%20get%20photographed%20with%20Russian%20foreign%20minister%20Sergei%20Lavrov%2C%20both%20laughing%20heartily%20and%20shaking%20hands%3B%20and%20he%20kept%20Africa%20happy%2C%20getting%20the%20African%20Union%20into%20the%20G20%20(though%20the%20idea%20was%20originally%20China%E2%80%99s).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20balancing%20Big%20Powers%20and%20voicing%20the%20views%20of%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20or%20Third%20World%20as%20Biden%20would%20say%2C%20to%20project%20India%E2%80%99s%20global%20personality%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20walked%20in%20the%20footsteps%20of%20prime%20minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru.%20He%20may%20not%20like%20being%20told%20that%2C%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20it%20was.%20%E2%80%98Multi-alignment%20and%20Voice%20of%20Global%20South%E2%80%99%20is%20New%20India%E2%80%99s%20version%20of%20Old%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Non-alignment%20and%20Third%20World%20Solidarity%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fsanjaya-baru%5C%22%3ESanjaya%20Baru%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20writer%20and%20policy%20analyst.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694440551000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F08123806%2FUntitled-design.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fg20-new-india-plays-an-old-game-walking-in-the-footsteps-of-nehru%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20may%20not%20like%20being%20told%20his%20'multi-alignment%20and%20voice%20of%20Global%20South'%20is%20New%20India's%20version%20of%20Old%20India's%20'non-alignment%20and%20Third%20World%20solidarity'.%C2%A0%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Remembering%209%2F11%20Speech%20of%20Swami%20Vivekananda%20That%20Warned%20Us%20of%20the%20Dangers%20Posed%20by%20Fanaticism%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F02%2F07191646%2FSwami_Vivekananda_at_Parliament_of_Religions.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EToday%20is%209%2F11%2C%202023.%20Normally%2C%20we%20remember%209%2F11%20for%20the%20terrorist%20attack%20on%20America%20in%202001%20by%20some%20fanatics%20who%20destroyed%20Twin%20Towers%20in%20New%20York%20and%20assaulted%20other%20places.%209%2F11%20associated%20with%20India%E2%80%99s%20history%20is%20more%20sublime%20and%20constructive.%20On%20this%20day%2C%20on%209%2F11%2C%201893%2C%20Swami%20Vivekananda%20addressed%20the%20World%20Parliament%20of%20Religions%20in%20Chicago.%20On%20this%20day%20in%201906%2C%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20started%20his%20first%20Satyagraha%20in%20South%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFanaticism%20manifested%20in%20majoritarianism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESwami%20Vivekananda%E2%80%99s%20short%20and%20profound%209%2F11%20speech%20stirred%20the%20Americans%2C%20by%20casting%20a%20spell%20on%20them.%20Later%2C%20through%20his%20numerous%20lectures%20on%20spirituality%20and%20Vedanta%2C%20he%20made%20a%20deep%20impact%20on%20their%20minds.%20In%20that%20historic%20Chicago%20speech%2C%20he%20profoundly%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%9Csectarianism%2C%20bigotry%20and%20its%20horrible%20descendent%20fanaticism%20drenched%20the%20earth%20with%20the%20blood%20of%20innocents%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20hoped%20that%20the%20bell%20that%20tolled%20to%20announce%20the%20commencement%20of%20the%20World%20Parliament%20of%20Religions%20would%20be%20the%20death%20knell%20of%20fanaticism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20were%20indeed%20very%20stirring%20words.%20Hundred%20and%20eight%20years%20after%20Swami%20Vivekananda%20uttered%20those%20words%2C%20America%20was%20attacked%20by%20some%20fanatics.%20Unfortunately%2C%20in%202023%2C%20the%20world%2C%20and%20especially%20India%2C%20is%20now%20confronting%20the%20combination%20of%20sectarianism%2C%20bigotry%2C%20and%20fanaticism%20in%20the%20form%20of%20majoritarianism%20and%20the%20polarisation%20process%20triggered%20by%20those%20controlling%20the%20state%20apparatus%20of%20our%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECall%20for%20genocide%20and%20ethnic%20cleansing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20we%20are%20facing%20a%20relentless%20spread%20of%20hatred%20and%20violence%20in%20the%20name%20of%20religion.%20Calls%20for%20the%20genocide%20of%20minorities%2C%20and%20that%20too%20of%20Muslims%2C%20are%20being%20issued%20day%20in%20and%20day%20out%20from%20the%20so%20called%20Dharma%20Sansads%2C%20religious%20parliaments.%20They%20are%20also%20accompanied%20by%20sinister%20calls%20for%20comprehensive%20social%20and%20economic%20boycott%20of%20Muslims.%20Very%20recently%2C%20it%20happened%20in%20Nuh%20in%20Haryana%20where%20Muslims%20were%20targeted%20violently%2C%20they%20were%20asked%20to%20flee%20from%20their%20places%20of%20work%2C%20and%20their%20houses%20were%20bulldozed.%20The%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20high%20court%20took%20suo%20motu%20cognisance%20of%20the%20matter%20and%20asked%20in%20its%20order%20if%20it%20was%20an%20exercise%20in%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fharyana-hc-halts-demolitions-in-nuh-owaisi-accuses-khattar-administration-of-targeting-muslims%5C%22%3Eethnic%20cleansing%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9C.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F02105412%2F1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F02105412%2F1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F02105412%2F1-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F02105412%2F1-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666220%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EStones%20and%20bricks%20used%20in%20the%20riots%20can%20be%20seen%20everywhere%20in%20Nuh.%20Photo%3A%20Atul%20Ashok%20Howale%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20shocking%20that%20the%20orders%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20the%20states%20where%20such%20calls%20for%20genocide%20and%20social%20and%20economic%20boycott%20are%20being%20issued%20are%20being%20ignored.%20In%20the%20recent%20past%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20wondered%20if%20the%20state%20of%20Maharashtra%20had%20become%20impotent%20to%20deal%20with%20hate%20speeches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fin-photos-from-vehicles-to-a-police-station-nuh-looks-deserted-burnt-after-violence%5C%22%3EIn%20Photos%3A%20From%20Vehicles%20to%20a%20Police%20Station%2C%20Nuh%20Looks%20Deserted%2C%20Burnt%20After%20Violence%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20unprecedented%20violence%20and%20bloodshed%20in%20Manipur%20on%20ethnic%20lines%20is%20sadly%20continuing.%20Unimaginable%20brutality%20suffered%20by%20women%20and%20the%20videos%20of%20brutal%20sexual%20violence%20against%20them%20on%20ethnic%20grounds%20bring%20out%20ghastly%20manifestations%20of%20sectarianism%20and%20bigotry%20which%20Swami%20Vivekananda%20flagged%20and%20cautioned%20about%20its%20horrible%20descendent%20fanaticism.%20He%20would%20have%20been%20deeply%20anguished%20to%20see%20that%20the%20words%20he%20uttered%20on%209%2F11%2C%201893%20%C2%A0are%20being%20ignored%20in%20India%2C%20which%20he%20said%2C%20gave%20shelter%20to%20those%20persecuted%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20religion%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESurvival%20of%20a%20nation%20endangered%20by%20hatred%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESwamiji%20had%20cautioned%20that%20the%20very%20sustenance%20of%20a%20nation%20would%20be%20endangered%20by%20spreading%20hatred%20against%20others.%20He%20traced%20India%E2%80%99s%20decline%20in%20history%20to%20hate%20generated%20within%20society%20and%20cutting%20off%20all%20communication%20with%20fellow%20Indians%20by%20showing%20contempt%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20letter%20to%20his%20disciple%20Alasinga%20Perumal%20from%20the%20USA%20on%20October%2027%2C%201894%2C%20he%20sensitively%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20man%2C%20no%20nation%2C%20my%20son%2C%20can%20hate%20others%20and%20live.%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20doom%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwas%20sealed%20the%20very%20day%20they%20invented%20the%20word%20MLECHCHHA%20and%20stopped%20from%20communion%20with%20others.%E2%80%9D%20This%20letter%20is%20available%20in%20Volume%205%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3EComplete%20Works%20of%20Swami%20Vivekananda%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20its%20contents%20are%20of%20immense%20significance%20in%20the%20context%20of%20India%20of%202023%20where%20hatred%20in%20the%20name%20of%20faith%20is%20dividing%20Indians%2C%20and%20inter-faith%20communication%20and%20harmony%20are%20poisoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESupreme%20Court%20flagged%20the%20danger%20posed%20by%20fanaticism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESwami%20Vivekananda%E2%80%99s%20cautionary%20utterances%20of%209%2F11%2C%201893%20that%20%E2%80%9Csectarianism%2C%20bigotry%20and%20its%20horrible%20descendent%20fanaticism%20drenched%20the%20earth%20with%20the%20blood%20of%20innocents%E2%80%9D%20can%20be%20ignored%20at%20our%20own%20peril.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDanger%20posed%20by%20fanaticism%20was%20flagged%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20its%20judgment%20of%20October%2013%2C%202022%2C%20in%20its%20order%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flawcorner.in%2Fhijab-row-in-karnataka-a-summary%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAishat%20Shifa%20Versus%20The%20State%20of%20Karnataka%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20allowing%20Muslim%20girls%20to%20wear%20hijab%20anywhere%20in%20schools%20and%20colleges%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20the%20court%20relied%20upon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.education.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fupload_files%2Fmhrd%2Ffiles%2Fupload_document%2FSCHEME_EHV.pdf%5C%22%3ES.B.%20Chavan%20Committee%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%201999%2C%20which%20strongly%20recommended%20education%20about%20religions%20as%20an%20instrument%20of%20social%20cohesion%20and%20social%20and%20religious%20harmony.%20The%20court%20quoted%20its%20para%20which%20stated%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CValue-based%20education%20is%20likely%20to%20help%20the%20nation%20to%20fight%20against%20all%20kinds%20of%20prevailing%20fanaticism%2C%20ill%20will%2C%20violence%2C%20dishonesty%2C%20corruption%2C%20exploitation%20and%20drug%20abuse%20%E2%80%A6%E2%80%A6%E2%80%A6%E2%80%A6%E2%80%A6%20Let%20knowledge%2C%20like%20the%20sun%2C%20shine%20for%20all%20and%20that%20there%20should%20not%20be%20any%20room%20for%20narrow-mindedness%2C%20blind%20faith%20and%20dogma.%20For%20this%20purpose%20also%2C%20if%20the%20basic%20tenets%20of%20all%20religions%20over%20the%20world%20are%20learnt%2C%20it%20cannot%20be%20said%20that%20secularism%20would%20not%20survive.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EComposite%20vision%20of%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20a%20hundred%20years%20back%20Swami%20Vivekananda%20defined%20India%20in%20a%20very%20composite%20manner%20without%20relying%20on%20any%20one%20religion.%20He%20said%20that%20India%20needed%20a%20Vedantic%20brain%20and%20Islamic%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20an%20approach%20underlines%20a%20multi-faith%20approach%20to%20understand%20India%20in%20contrast%20to%20cultural%20nationalism%20which%20promotes%20uniformity%20and%20endangers%20multiculturalim.%20Those%20who%20swear%20by%20one%20nation%2C%20one%20culture%2C%20and%20one%20faith%20negate%20the%20vision%20of%20Swami%20Vivekananda%20whom%20they%20often%20hail%20as%20their%20icon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENehru%20and%20Ambedkar%20on%20Vedanta%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20fascinating%20to%20note%20that%20the%20Vedantic%20approach%20of%20Swami%20Vivekananda%20was%20mentioned%20by%20former%20prime%20minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20when%20he%20wrote%20in%20his%20famous%20paper%20%3Cem%3EBasic%20Approach%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20eventually%20a%20Vedantic%20outlook%20would%20provide%20solutions%20to%20many%20challenges%20of%20modern%20civilisation%2C%20which%20he%20said%2C%20caused%20mental%20exhaustion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr.%20B.R.Ambedkar%20while%20bitterly%20criticising%20Hinduism%20and%20describing%20it%20as%20a%20religion%20based%20on%20graded%20social%20inequality%20wrote%20in%20his%20essay%20on%20%3Cem%3EAnnihilation%20of%20Caste%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20India%20required%20a%20religion%20based%20on%20liberty%2C%20equality%2C%20and%20fraternity%2C%20and%20such%20a%20religion%20would%20derive%20sustenance%20from%20Upanishads.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20Upanishads%20constitute%20the%20Vedanta.%20It%20is%20instructive%20that%20both%20prime%20minister%20Nehru%20and%20Dr.%20Ambedkar%2C%20builders%20of%20modern%20India%2C%20stressed%20on%20Vedantic%20approach%2C%20which%20was%20prescribed%20by%20Swami%20Vivekananda%20along%20with%20the%20values%20of%20Islam%20to%20conjure%20up%20the%20vision%20of%20India.%20It%20is%20important%20to%20remain%20anchored%20in%20the%20vision%20articulated%20by%20Swami%20Vivekananda%20on%209%2F11%2C%201893%2C%20to%20defeat%20fanaticism%20threatening%20the%20very%20Idea%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ES.%20N.%20Sahu%20served%20as%20Officer%20on%20Special%20Duty%20to%20President%20of%20India%20K.R.%20Narayanan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694439033000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fremembering-9-11-s