1%2Fchile-is-still-haunted-by-the-coup-in-september-1973%5C%22%3ECIA%20admitted%20later%20that%20it%20had%20engineered%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAllende%E2%80%99s%20coming%20to%20power%20was%20the%20first%20historical%20example%20of%20a%20socialist%2FMarxist%20movement%20gaining%20success%20in%20country%20through%20democratic%20means%20in%20an%20election%20battle%20with%20the%20right-wing%20parties.%20This%20was%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20with%20the%20Bolshevik%20Revolution%20of%201917%2C%20Chinese%20Revolution%20in%201949%20and%20Cuban%20Revolution%20in%201959.%20Kerala%20in%20India%20in%201957%20is%20generally%20cited%20as%20the%20first%20example%20of%20communists%20coming%20to%20power%20through%20the%20electoral%20process%3B%20but%20this%20victory%2C%20though%20very%20important%2C%20was%20confined%20to%20a%20state%20in%20a%20big%20country%20and%20did%20not%20have%20the%20same%20international%20significance%20as%20the%20Chilean%20success%20under%20Allende%E2%80%99s%20leadership.%20It%20was%20precisely%20this%20democratic%20Chileans%20path%20to%20socialism%20which%20scared%20the%20anti-socialist%20global%20establishment%20led%20by%20the%20US%2C%20and%20that%20too%20geographically%20so%20close%20to%20the%20US.%20The%20US%20was%20already%20trying%20to%20crush%20Cuba%E2%80%99s%20turn%20to%20socialism%20through%20economic%20blockades%20and%20military%20intrusions%20and%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22America%E2%80%99s%20First%20Date%20with%209%2F11%20Was%20Not%20on%20US%20Soil%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Famericas-first-date-with-9-11-was-not-on-us-soil%5C%22%3EAmerica%E2%80%99s%20First%20Date%20with%209%2F11%20Was%20Not%20on%20US%20Soil%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChile%E2%80%99s%20turn%20to%20socialism%20was%20even%20more%20threatening%20to%20the%20US%20establishment%20than%20Cuba%20because%20of%20five%20reasons%3A%20one%2C%20it%20was%20an%20economically%20successful%20economy%20with%20very%20good%20resource%20base%20especially%20in%20copper%2C%20two%2C%20another%20socialist%20country%20in%20Latin%20America%20along%20with%20Cuba%20was%20seen%20as%20encouraging%20anti-American%20bloc%20in%20the%20US%20sphere%20of%20influence%2C%20third%2C%20the%20democratic%20Chilean%20path%20to%20socialism%20was%20seen%20by%20the%20US%20as%20a%20possible%20example%20to%20other%20countries%20in%20Latin%20America%20to%20follow%20the%20socialist%20path%20in%20contrast%20with%20doubts%20in%20those%20countries%20about%20following%20the%20Cuba%20style%20guerrilla%20path%20of%20armed%20capture%20of%20state%20power%2C%20fourth%2C%20very%20big%20multinational%20corporations%20in%20the%20US%20had%20long%20established%20business%20interests%20in%20Chile%20especially%20in%20copper%2C%20and%20fifth%2C%20Chile%20in%20addition%20to%20Cuba%20was%20seen%20as%20strengthening%20the%20Soviet%20sphere%20of%20influence%20in%20Latin%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20due%20to%20these%20reasons%20that%20the%20US%20started%20campaigns%20and%20strategies%20to%20unseat%20Allende%20from%20power.%20One%20of%20the%20first%20significant%20economic%20sabotage%20campaigns%20organised%20by%20the%20CIA%20was%20to%20finance%20the%20anti-socialist%20opposition%20to%20organise%20a%20nationwide%20strike%20by%20truck-drivers%20and%20shop%20keepers.%20Geographically%2C%20Chilean%20territory%20is%20characterised%20by%20length%20and%20very%20narrow%20in%20breadth.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20strike%20by%20the%20truck%20drivers%20crippled%20the%20transport%20system%20in%20the%20country.%20US%20blocked%20loans%20to%20Chile.%20The%20Richard%20Nixon-led%20administration%20in%20the%20US%20openly%20supported%20CIA%20led%20sabotage%20of%20Allende-led%20Chile%20and%20directed%20the%20CIA%20to%20make%20Chile%E2%80%99s%20economy%20scream.%20These%20sabotage%20campaigns%20gave%20push%20to%20shortages%20and%20high%20inflation.%20Allende%20still%20retained%20his%20popularity%20but%20also%20sought%20military%20support%20to%20his%20regime%20by%20bringing%20some%20military%20commanders%20into%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20programme%20of%20nationalisation%20of%20copper%20mines%20started%20by%20Allende%E2%80%99s%20government%20especially%20alarmed%20the%20US%20corporations%20and%20their%20allies%20in%20the%20US%20military%20and%20Chilean%20military.%20The%20nationalisation%20of%20copper%20mines%20was%20internally%20so%20popular%20in%20Chile%20that%20even%20the%20opposition%20supported%20it.%20The%20Allende%20government%20proceeded%20to%20issue%20a%20decree%20for%20state%20takeover%20of%20150%20large%20firms.%20Some%20left%20adventurist%20supporters%20of%20the%20government%20went%20on%20a%20spree%20of%20illegal%20seizure%20of%20many%20businesses%2C%20farms%20and%20even%20houses.%20This%20left%20adventurism%20caused%20unease%20with%20some%20sections%20of%20the%20middle%20class%20which%20had%20previously%20supported%20the%20Allende%20government%E2%80%99s%20measures%20of%20wage%20increases%20and%20expansion%20of%20public%20sector%20jobs.%20The%20country%20was%20getting%20increasingly%20polarised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERumours%20started%20circulating%20that%20military%20might%20stage%20a%20coup.%20Allende%2C%20despite%20being%20a%20militant%2C%20believed%20in%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20trusted%20the%20Chilean%20constitution%20that%20military%20would%20remain%20neutral%20in%20political%20contestation.%20Many%20of%20his%20supporters%20held%20huge%20rallies%20in%20his%20support%20with%20a%20demand%20for%20weapons%20to%20defend%20his%20government.%20This%20led%20to%20unjustified%20and%20deliberate%20propaganda%20that%20his%20supporters%20were%20acquiring%20weapons%20for%20a%20military%20confrontation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20military%20led%20by%20General%20August%20Pinochet%20staged%20the%20coup.%20The%20military%20entered%20the%20presidential%20place.%20Allende%20did%20not%20surrender%20and%20died%20fighting.%20It%20is%20still%20uncertain%20whether%20he%20shot%20himself%20or%20was%20killed%20by%20the%20army.%20He%2C%20however%2C%20managed%20to%20broadcast%20a%20seven-minute%20historically%20significant%20message%20to%20the%20nation%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20will%20not%20resign.%20I%20will%20repay%20the%20loyalty%20of%20the%20people%20with%20my%20life%E2%80%A6%20Always%20remember%20that%20much%20sooner%20that%20later%20the%20great%20avenues%20along%20which%20free%20men%20pass%20to%20build%20a%20better%20society%20will%20once%20again%20be%20open.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FIZVWOWA2Hpk%3Fsi%3DbOablZFCu4FjVhws%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFifteen%20years%20of%20military%20dictatorship%20(1973-1988)%20of%20Pinochet%20followed.%20This%20was%20one%20of%20the%20worst%20periods%20for%20human%20rights%20violations%20in%20any%20country.%20Chile%20entered%20a%20period%20of%20darkness.%20Trade%20unionists%2C%20academics%2C%20journalists%2C%20lawyers%20and%20students%20were%20arrested%2C%20tortured%20and%20disappeared.%20The%20military%20junta%20murdered%202%2C130%20people%20and%20tortured%20at%20least%2030%2C000%2C%20some%20very%20brutally%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2004%2Fnov%2F15%2Fchile.jonathanfranklin%5C%22%3Einvestigations%20by%20democratic%20governments%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20came%20to%20power%20after%201988.%20The%20narratives%20I%20heard%20in%20Oxford%20from%20some%20victims%20of%20Pinochet%E2%80%99s%20terror%20regime%2C%20which%20was%20also%20very%20corrupt%20like%20all%20dictatorships%2C%20have%20been%20horrifying.%20Pinochet%20was%20eventually%20arrested%20in%20London%20in%201998%20by%20an%20order%20passed%20by%20a%20great%20Spanish%20Judge%20Baltasar%20Garzon%20under%20an%20international%20law%20that%20anyone%20responsible%20for%20torture%20and%20disappearance%20of%20political%20prisoners%20in%20a%20country%20can%20be%20arrested%20even%20outside%20that%20country.%20This%20was%20a%20landmark%20case%20in%20strengthening%20the%20idea%20of%20universal%20jurisdiction%20for%20crimes%20against%20humanity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22The%20Day%20Chile%20and%20the%20Rest%20of%20Latin%20America%20Remember%20as%20Their%209%2F11%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthe-day-chileans-and-the-rest-of-latin-america-remember-their-911%5C%22%3EThe%20Day%20Chile%20and%20the%20Rest%20of%20Latin%20America%20Remember%20as%20Their%209%2F11%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPinochet%20died%20a%20disgraced%20man%20in%202011%20while%20Allende%20has%20entered%20Chilean%20and%20global%20history%20as%20an%20icon%20of%20progress%20and%20justice.%20The%20current%20president%20of%20Chile%2C%20Gabriel%20Boric%2C%20paid%20homage%20on%20his%20day%20of%20inauguration%20to%20Allende%20at%20his%20statue%20in%20front%20of%20La%20Moneda%2C%20the%20presidential%20palace%20in%20the%20capital%20Santiago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20will%20remain%20a%20very%20black%20spot%20in%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20the%20international%20political%20order%20that%20it%20engineered%20this%20most%20dreadful%20military%20coup%20of%20a%20democratically%20elected%20leader.%20It%20is%20also%20a%20black%20spot%20in%20the%20history%20of%20the%20Chicago%20School%20of%20Economics%2C%20which%20led%20by%20Milton%20Freedman%20advised%20the%20dictator%20Pinochet%20to%20launch%20the%20neoliberal%20programme%20of%20privatisation%20and%20dismantling%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20providing%20public%20utilities.%20For%20the%20socialists%20in%20Chile%20and%20outside%2C%20Allende%20remains%20a%20source%20of%20inspiration%20while%20recognising%20that%20the%20new%20era%20of%20socialist%20vision%20must%20incorporate%20the%20ecological%20perspective%20in%20dealing%20with%20the%20threat%20of%20global%20climate%20change%20being%20hastened%20under%20capitalism.%20The%20eco-socialist%20vision%20must%20eschew%20the%20old%20socialist%20fascination%20with%20fast%20industrialisation%20and%20economic%20growth.%20Building%20a%20broader%20alliance%20of%20forces%20to%20forge%20a%20consensus%20for%20building%20a%20fairer%2C%20equitable%20and%20sustainable%20future%20of%20humanity%20would%20be%20the%20most%20appropriate%20way%20of%20paying%20homage%20to%20Allende%20and%20the%20thousands%20of%20socialist%20martyrs%20of%20Chile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPritam%20Singh%20is%20Professor%20Emeritus%20at%20Oxford%20Brookes%20Business%20School%20and%20the%20author%20of%20Economy%2C%20Culture%20and%20Human%20Rights.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694419847000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F11133907%2F8284617884_3171c96d6a_o.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fremembering-salvador-allendes-socialist-chile-50-years-on%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20will%20remain%20a%20very%20black%20spot%20in%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20the%20international%20political%20order%20that%20it%20engineered%20a%20most%20dreadful%20military%20coup%20of%20a%20democratically%20elected%20leader.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A41%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fremembering-salvador-allendes-socialist-chile-50-years-on%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Civil%20Society%20Calls%20Out%20G20%20Declaration%E2%80%99s%20Omission%20of%20Civic%20Space%20Erosion%2C%20Democracy%20Decline%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F08133538%2F2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20G20%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20Declaration%2C%20following%20the%20New%20Delhi%20Summit%2C%20has%20drawn%20criticism%20from%20civil%20society%20organisations%20for%20its%20inadequacy%20in%20addressing%20critical%20global%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Declaration%20falls%20short%20in%20offering%20a%20clear%20roadmap%20to%20tackle%20the%20pressing%20concerns%20of%20economic%20inequality%2C%20climate%20crisis%2C%20hunger%2C%20and%20energy%20issues%2C%20Peoples%E2%80%99%2020%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20Monday%2C%20September%2011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Summit%20itself%20was%20marred%20by%20controversy%2C%20with%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbeautification%20drive%E2%80%9D%20displacing%20slum%20residents.%20Meanwhile%2C%20reports%20of%20ethnic%20violence%20against%20the%20Christian%20minority%20were%20reported%20in%20Northeast%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Declaration%2C%20a%20result%20of%20intense%20negotiations%20among%20G20%20member%20nations%2C%20also%20lacks%20a%20comprehensive%20reassessment%20of%20neoliberal%20market-driven%20economies%20and%20GDP-centric%20growth%20paradigms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20raised%20concerns%20over%20the%20Declaration%E2%80%99s%20omission%20of%20critical%20issues%20such%20as%20the%20erosion%20of%20civic%20space%20and%20the%20global%20decline%20in%20democracy.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20alarming%20trend%20is%20especially%20pertinent%20in%20several%20G20%20countries%2C%20including%20China%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Russia%2C%20T%C3%BCrkiye%2C%20Mexico%2C%20and%20India%2C%20as%20highlighted%20by%20CIVICUS%E2%80%99s%20Civic%20Space%20Monitor%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Ffive-keys-takeaways-from-the-g20-summit-in-delhi%5C%22%3EFive%20Keys%20Takeaways%20From%20the%20G20%20Summit%20in%20Delhi%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20text%20of%20the%20full%20statement%20is%20reproduced%20below%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EG20%20Falls%20Short%20in%20Addressing%20Global%20Challenges%2C%20Promises%20Abound%20but%20Impact%20Lacks%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECivil%20society%20organizations%20(CSOs)%20are%20raising%20their%20voices%20in%20dissent%20as%20they%20criticize%20the%20G20%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20Declaration%20for%20its%20inability%20to%20confront%20the%20most%20critical%20global%20issues.%20Despite%20its%20grandiose%20language%2C%20the%20Declaration%20falls%20short%20in%20offering%20concrete%20commitments%20and%20a%20clear%20roadmap%20to%20tackle%20the%20pressing%20concerns%20of%20rising%20economic%20inequality%2C%20climate%20crisis%2C%20hunger%2C%20and%20the%20energy%20crisis.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20G20%20New%20Delhi%20Summit%20unfolded%20amid%20controversy%2C%20marked%20by%20a%20contentious%20%E2%80%9Cbeautification%20drive%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20event.%20This%20drive%20resulted%20in%20the%20displacement%20of%20numerous%20slum%20residents%20as%20their%20homes%20were%20bulldozed.%20Additionally%2C%20there%20was%20a%20crackdown%20on%20civil%20society%20gatherings%20critical%20of%20the%20G20%20summit%2C%20and%20troubling%20incidents%20of%20ethnic%20violence%20against%20the%20Christian%20minority%20in%20Northeast%20India%20were%20reported.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20G20%20Summit%20took%20place%20amidst%20one%20of%20the%20most%20polarized%20periods%20in%20its%20history%2C%20harkening%20back%20to%20the%20turbulence%20of%202008.%20The%20Declaration%2C%20adopted%20on%20the%20first%20day%20of%20the%20Summit%2C%20represents%20the%20outcome%20of%20extensive%20negotiations%20among%20member%20nations%20grappling%20with%20divergent%20interests%2C%20including%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWe%20extend%20our%20congratulations%20to%20the%20Indian%20government%20for%20skillfully%20facilitating%20the%20negotiation%20process%20that%20culminated%20in%20the%20consensus%20document%2C%20a%20product%20of%20compromise%20among%20the%2020%20member%20states%20grappling%20with%20conflicting%20priorities.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EComprising%20over%2014%2C000%20words%2C%20the%20Declaration%20delves%20into%20a%20wide%20spectrum%20of%20global%20economic%2C%20social%2C%20and%20environmental%20issues.%20In%20comparison%20to%20the%202022%20Bali%20Declaration%2C%20it%20provides%20a%20more%20substantial%20treatment%20of%20topics%20such%20as%20the%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20(SDGs)%2C%20gender%20equality%2C%20women%E2%80%99s%20empowerment%2C%20and%20digital%20technology%2C%20including%20Artificial%20Intelligence%20issues.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENevertheless%2C%20beneath%20its%20eloquent%20rhetoric%2C%20the%20Declaration%20falls%20short%20in%20providing%20substantial%20analysis%20and%20tangible%20solutions%20for%20the%20pressing%20global%20crises.%20These%20crises%2C%20including%20escalating%20social%2C%20economic%2C%20political%20and%20ecological%20inequalities%20and%20climate%20and%20biodiversity%C2%A0%20threats%2C%20have%20far-reaching%20consequences%20affecting%20not%20only%20G20%20nations%20but%20also%20non-G20%20countries%2C%20particularly%20those%20in%20the%20developing%20world%20and%20countries%20in%20conflict%2C%20which%20are%20highly%20susceptible%20to%20external%20economic%20and%20ecological%20shocks.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20the%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration%20of%20the%20PEOPLES%E2%80%99%2020%20Assembly%20held%20on%20August%2023-24%2C%202023%2C%20we%20fervently%20called%20upon%20G20%20leaders%20to%20display%20resolute%20collective%20determination%20in%20reshaping%20the%20existing%20political%20and%20economic%20framework.%20This%20framework%20has%20contributed%20to%20the%20global%20crisis%20by%20prioritizing%20narrow%20national%20and%20elite%20interests%2C%20exploitative%20extractive%20industry%2C%20fossil%20fuel%20and%20carbon-based%20growth%20models%2C%20global%20value%20chains%20that%20disrespect%20human%20and%20labour%20rights%2C%20and%20military%20security%20considerations.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20G20%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20Declaration%20fails%20to%20conduct%20a%20thorough%20reassessment%20of%20neoliberal%20market-driven%20economies%20and%20the%20GDP-centric%20growth%20paradigm.%20It%20offers%20little%20indication%20of%20genuine%20efforts%20to%20explore%20alternative%20paradigms%20rooted%20in%20ecological%20sustainability%2C%20inclusive%20human%20development%2C%20human%20security%2C%20positive%20peace%2C%20gender%20equality%2C%20and%20social%20justice.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMuch%20to%20their%20dismay%2C%20we%20perceive%20a%20perpetuation%20of%20the%20status%20quo%20and%20a%20business-as-usual%20approach%20in%20the%20G20%E2%80%99s%20actions%2C%20ignoring%20the%20deepening%20global%20crisis.%20While%20the%20G20%20leaders%20managed%20to%20reach%20a%20consensus%20on%20the%20Declaration%2C%20the%20unprecedented%20fragmentation%20and%20division%20within%20the%20G20%20cast%20significant%20doubt%20on%20its%20normative%20and%20political%20legitimacy%20and%20effectiveness.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWhile%20we%20appreciate%20the%20Declaration%E2%80%99s%20inclusion%20of%20an%20extensive%20list%20of%20commitments%2C%20we%20cannot%20help%20but%20harbor%20doubts%20about%20its%20practical%20effectiveness.%20These%20doubts%20stem%20from%20the%20absence%20of%20concrete%2C%20time-bound%20action%20plans%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20an%20independent%20accountability%20and%20monitoring%20mechanism%20to%20assess%20their%20implementation.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThere%20has%20been%20an%20undue%20emphasis%20on%20the%20role%20of%20the%20private%20sector%20in%20economic%20development.%20We%20are%20concerned%20about%20the%20potential%20for%20corporate%20influence%20on%20government%20policies%20and%20multilateral%20organizations%20such%20as%20the%20UN.%20We%20notice%20the%20absence%20to%20a%20reference%20on%20ongoing%20efforts%20in%20several%20G20%20countries%20and%20regions%20(EU%20and%20AU)%20for%20due%20diligence%20laws%20for%20global%20value%20chains%20and%20the%20ongoing%20negotiations%20for%20a%20binding%20treaty%20on%20business%20and%20human%20rights.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENotably%2C%20there%20has%20been%20insufficient%20progress%20on%20critical%20issues%20such%20as%20the%20waiving%20of%20patent%20rights%2C%20which%20obstructs%20access%20to%20vital%20COVID-19%20and%20other%20life-saving%20medications.%20The%20Declaration%20also%20falls%20short%20in%20addressing%20global%20taxation%20and%20a%20UN-based%20tax%20body%2C%20and%20reform%20of%20the%20international%20financial%20architecture%2C%20guided%20by%20principles%20of%20global%20equality%20and%20justice.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt%20is%20deeply%20disappointing%20to%20witness%20a%20lack%20of%20commitment%20to%20debt%20cancellation%20for%20the%2060%20countries%20that%20are%20most%20severely%20burdened%20by%20their%20debt%20obligations.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWe%20are%20deeply%20concerned%20that%20the%20Declaration%20has%20largely%20disregarded%20policy%20recommendations%20presented%20by%20Civil%20Society%20Organizations%20(CSOs)%2C%20despite%20the%20dedicated%20efforts%20of%20engagement%20groups%20and%20independent%20CSOs.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20process%20has%20denied%20access%20to%20human%20rights-based%20civil%20society%20and%20trade%20union%20movements%2C%20which%20is%20equally%20troubling.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWe%20express%20profound%20concern%20over%20the%20Declaration%E2%80%99s%20omission%20of%20critical%20issues%20such%20as%20the%20erosion%20of%20civic%20space%20and%20the%20global%20decline%20in%20democracy.%20This%20alarming%20trend%20is%20especially%20pertinent%20in%20several%20G20%20countries%2C%20including%20China%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Russia%2C%20T%C3%BCrkiye%2C%20Mexico%2C%20and%20India%2C%20as%20highlighted%20by%20CIVICUS%E2%80%99s%20Civic%20Space%20Monitor.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFurthermore%2C%20it%20was%20disappointing%20to%20note%20that%20the%20Declaration%20made%20no%20reference%20to%20vital%20concepts%20such%20as%20democracy%2C%20civil%20society%2C%20and%20youth%2C%20despite%20the%20host%20country%2C%20India%2C%20proudly%20proclaiming%20itself%20as%20the%20mother%20of%20democracy.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2030%20Agenda%20for%20Sustainable%20Development%20and%20the%20SDGs%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%202023%20G20%20Summit%20was%20a%20timely%20opportunity%2C%20situated%20midway%20to%202030%2C%20for%20taking%20stock%20and%20assessing%20global%20progress%20on%20the%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20(SDGs).%20We%20welcome%20the%20G20%20leaders%E2%80%99%20acknowledgment%20that%20%E2%80%9Cglobal%20progress%20on%20SDGs%20is%20off-track%2C%20with%20only%2012%20percent%20of%20the%20targets%20on%20track.%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWe%20also%20recognize%20the%20G20%20leaders%E2%80%99%20commitment%20to%20leveraging%20the%20G20%E2%80%99s%20convening%20power%20and%20collective%20determination%20to%20fully%20implement%20the%202030%20Agenda%20and%20expedite%20progress%20towards%20the%20SDGs.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt%20is%20worth%20noting%20that%20while%20much%20was%20discussed%20regarding%20the%20SDGs%2C%20there%20was%20a%20lack%20of%20concrete%20commitment%20to%20the%20500%20billion%20SDG%20Stimulus%20Fund.%20While%20the%20G20%20commits%20to%20supporting%20the%20full%20and%20effective%20implementation%20of%20the%20SDGs%2C%20it%20fails%20to%20propose%20strategies%20that%20can%20effectively%20realize%20these%20targets%20for%20vulnerable%20populations%20that%20are%20at%20risk%20of%20being%20left%20behind.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20principle%20of%20%E2%80%9Cleave%20no%20one%20behind%E2%80%9D%20was%20not%20effectively%20implemented%2C%20as%20the%20Declaration%20lacked%20specific%20policies%20catering%20to%20the%20rights%20and%20needs%20of%20vulnerable%20and%20marginalized%20groups%2C%20including%20migrants%2C%20indigenous%20peoples%2C%20social%20and%20ethnic%20minorities%20like%20Dalits%2C%20persons%20with%20disabilities%2C%20and%20small-scale%20farmers.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWe%20urgently%20call%20upon%20all%20G20%20countries%2C%20particularly%20the%20United%20States%2C%20to%20engage%20more%20actively%20in%20the%20Voluntary%20National%20Review%20(VNR)%20process%20as%20a%20demonstration%20of%20their%20commitment%20to%20aligning%20their%20policies%20with%20the%202030%20Agenda%20for%20Sustainable%20Development%20and%20and%20reporting%20on%20their%20progress%20and%20challenges.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWhile%20we%20acknowledge%20the%20G20%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20quality%20and%20cyber%20education%2C%20we%20emphasize%20the%20paramount%20importance%20of%20universal%20basic%20education%20for%20all%2C%20alongside%20the%20significant%20challenges%20posed%20by%20the%20digital%20divide%20both%20within%20and%20among%20countries.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWe%20wholeheartedly%20applaud%20the%20decision%20to%20grant%20permanent%20membership%20to%20the%20African%20Union%20(AU)%20within%20the%20G20%2C%20signifying%20a%20pivotal%20step%20towards%20greater%20inclusivity%20and%20representation.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWhile%20the%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20(SDGs)%20aim%20for%20universalizing%2012%20years%20of%20schooling%2C%20the%20G20%20discusses%20foundational%20learning%20and%20does%20not%20commit%20to%20the%20SDG%20targets%2C%20marking%20a%20step%20backward.%20The%20G20%20also%20places%20significant%20emphasis%20on%20technical%20and%20vocational%20education%20and%20digital%20education.%20However%2C%20without%20access%20to%20secondary%20education%2C%20these%20initiatives%20become%20dead%20ends%20and%20do%20not%20adequately%20foster%20youth%20development.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20Declaration%20discusses%20facilitating%20migration%20for%20skilled%20workers%2C%20mapping%20skills%20gaps%2C%20and%20providing%20skills%20training%2C%20among%20other%20topics.%20However%2C%20it%20notably%20excludes%20the%20large%20majority%20of%20unskilled%20workers%20from%20the%20global%20south%20who%20migrate%20to%20developed%20countries%2C%20such%20as%20construction%20workers%2C%20domestic%20workers%2C%20and%20plantation%20workers.%20It%20is%20crucial%20that%20facilitation%20and%20protection%20measures%20also%20encompass%20these%20workers%2C%20as%20they%20play%20a%20vital%20role%20by%20sending%20valuable%20remittances%20to%20their%20home%20countries%20and%20serving%20as%20the%20mainstay%20for%20their%20impoverished%20families.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGender%20Equality%20and%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Empowerment%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20declaration%20instrumentalizes%20gender%20equality%20for%20economic%20growth%20instead%20of%20recognizing%20it%20as%20a%20fundamental%20human%20right.%20It%20fails%20to%20acknowledge%20intersectionality%20and%20the%20diversity%20among%20women.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20establishment%20of%20a%20new%20Working%20Group%20on%20the%20Empowerment%20of%20Women%20is%20a%20positive%20development.%20We%20hope%20it%20will%20significantly%20contribute%20to%20expediting%20progress%20towards%20the%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20(SDGs)%20by%20adopting%20a%20gender-equal%2C%20transformative%2C%20and%20inclusive%20approach%20across%20all%20dimensions%20of%20the%202030%20Agenda.%20We%20also%20hope%20that%20this%20effort%20will%20complement%20the%20work%20of%20UN%20Women%2C%20Women%2020%2C%20and%20collaborate%20with%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Major%20Group%20and%20the%20Women%20and%20Gender%20Constituency%2C%20rather%20than%20creating%20another%20parallel%20process%20that%20consumes%20additional%20time%20and%20resources.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWe%20warmly%20welcome%20the%20commitment%20to%20respect%20religious%20diversity%20and%20tolerance%20(paragraph%2078)%2C%20which%20highlights%20the%20significance%20of%20both%20freedom%20of%20religion%20or%20belief%20and%20the%20rights%20to%20peaceful%20assembly%20and%20freedom%20of%20association.%20Once%20more%2C%20we%20emphasize%20the%20crucial%20need%20for%20an%20explicit%20reference%20to%20human%20rights%20and%20labor%20rights%20conventions.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecurity%20and%20Nuclear%20Weapons%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20emphasis%20on%20international%20security%20was%20notable%2C%20but%20there%20was%20a%20glaring%20absence%20of%20attention%20to%20the%20escalating%20military%20expenditures%2C%20arms%20proliferation%2C%20and%20the%20military-industrial%20complex%20among%20G20%20member%20states.%20We%20strongly%20urge%20G20%20countries%20to%20redirect%20currently%20exploding%20military%20spending%20towards%20climate%20loss%20and%20damage%20funds%20and%20the%20SDG%20stimulus%20fund.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWe%20appreciate%20the%20reaffirmation%20of%20the%20inadmissibility%20of%20the%20use%20or%20threat%20of%20use%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%2C%20as%20previously%20expressed%20in%20the%20Bali%202022%20Declaration.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20essential%20to%20establish%20effective%20implementation%20mechanisms%2C%20such%20as%20a%20No%20First%20Use%20policy%20or%20a%20multilateral%20mutual%20non-use%20and%20non-threat%20commitment.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERegrettably%2C%20the%20Declaration%20does%20not%20include%20any%20mention%20of%20the%20ratification%20of%20the%20Treaty%20for%20the%20Prohibition%20of%20Nuclear%20Weapons%20(TPNW).%20We%20call%20upon%20all%20six%20nuclear-armed%20G20%20nations%2C%20namely%20China%2C%20France%2C%20Russia%2C%20India%2C%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20the%20UK%2C%20to%20demonstrate%20their%20responsibility%20for%20global%20human%20security%20by%20taking%20meaningful%20action%20on%20this%20matter.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollow-up%20and%20Next%20G20%20Summit%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWe%20recognize%20the%20G20%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20%E2%80%9Cprovide%20full%20support%20to%20the%20UN%202023%20SDGs%20Summit%20and%20the%20UN%202024%20Summit%20of%20the%20Future.%E2%80%9D%20As%20G20%20countries%20are%20also%20UN%20members%2C%20they%20have%20the%20opportunity%20to%20showcase%20their%20leadership%20by%20fulfilling%20their%20obligations%20and%20commitments.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWith%20Brazil%20set%20to%20host%20the%20G20%20Summit%20in%202024%20and%20South%20Africa%20in%202025%2C%20it%20is%20imperative%20that%20the%20G20%20takes%20immediate%2C%20radical%20action%20on%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20Time%20is%20of%20the%20essence.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECSOs%20strongly%20urge%20G20%20leaders%2C%20especially%20those%20of%20Brazil%20and%20South%20Africa%2C%20to%20delve%20deeper%20into%20the%20root%20causes%20of%20these%20global%20crises%20and%20challenges%2C%20working%20proactively%20to%20prevent%20their%20recurrence%20in%20partnership%20with%20civil%20society.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAbout%20PEOPLES%3B%2020%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPEOPLES%E2%80%99%2020%20is%20a%20worldwide%20network%20and%20initiative%20composed%20of%20civil%20society%20actors%20and%20organizations%20that%20willingly%20participate%20in%20the%20G20%20summit%20and%20associated%20processes.%20This%20initiative%20was%20formally%20inaugurated%20on%20March%201%2C%202023%2C%20following%20a%20series%20of%20consultation%20meetings%20involving%20CSOs%20in%20India%20and%20from%20around%20the%20world%20who%20have%20been%20actively%20engaged%20with%20the%20G20%20since%202010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPEOPLES%E2%80%99%2020%20convened%20its%20own%20Assembly%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20August%2023-24%2C%202023%2C%20during%20which%20it%20adopted%20the%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration%20and%20the%20Policy%20Pack%20on%20the%20G20%20Summit.%20This%20package%20encapsulates%20the%20policy%20recommendations%20put%20forth%20by%20CSOs%20and%20citizens%20hailing%20from%20both%20G20%20and%20non-G20%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694418642000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F08133538%2F2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fcivil-society-calls-out-g20-declarations-omission-of-civic-space-erosion-democracy-decline%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20G20%20Declaration%20falls%20short%20in%20offering%20a%20clear%20roadmap%20to%20tackle%20the%20pressing%20concerns%20of%20economic%20inequality%2C%20climate%20crisis%2C%20hunger%2C%20and%20energy%20issues%2C%20Peoples'%2020%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20G20%20Has%20Summarily%20Failed%20to%20Address%20Agrarian%20Distress%20in%20its%20Member%20Countries%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F11125829%2FUntitled-design-1-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENew%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20hosting%20of%20the%20G20%20summit%20opened%20a%20window%20to%20observe%20India%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20goals.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20summit%20was%20broken%20by%20the%20absence%20of%20Chinese%20and%20Russian%20presidents%20Vladimir%20Putin%20and%20Xi%20Jinping%2C%20but%20it%20did%20host%20world%20leaders%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fus-president-biden-says-he-raised-importance-of-human-rights-and-free-press-with-pm-modi%5C%22%3Eincluding%20the%20US%20president%20Joe%20Biden%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20all%20practical%20purposes%2C%20it%20is%20a%20known%20fact%20that%20the%20G20%20is%20the%20G7%20hiding%20in%20G20%E2%80%99s%20clothing%20and%20also%20pushing%20what%20is%20largely%20regarded%20as%20an%20American-Quad%20playbook.%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20various%20remarks%20to%20the%20US%20media%20before%20arriving%20in%20India%20had%20overtly%20expressed%20his%20desire%20to%20put%20%E2%80%9CAmerica%20first%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20G20.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20a%20successful%20BRICS%20conference%20in%20South%20Africa%2C%20complete%20with%20the%20addition%20of%20new%20members%2C%20US%20foreign%20policy%20had%20been%20keen%20to%20exert%20Quad%20influence%20on%20the%20G20%20too.%20Although%20the%20Russian%20and%20Chinese%20sides%20have%20come%20away%20with%20a%20significant%20victory%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fg20-modi-new-delhi-declaration-consensus%5C%22%3Ewith%20how%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20was%20handled%20in%20the%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20agriculture%20diplomacy%20in%20the%20run%20up%20to%20the%20G20%20shows%20that%20it%20has%20always%20been%20angling%20at%20honouring%20the%20G7%E2%80%99s%20motto.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBacking%20up%20to%20June%2C%20when%20G20%E2%80%99s%20agricultural%20ministers%20met%20in%20Hyderabad%2C%20it%20became%20clear%20that%20we%20had%20a%20major%20diplomatic%20and%20imminent%20global%20food%20crisis.%20This%20is%20because%20no%20global%20food%20system%20can%20reasonably%20function%20in%20current%20times%20without%20Russian%20wheat%20and%20fertilisers.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Russia%2C%20on%20September%209%20rejected%20the%20United%20Nation%E2%80%99s%20timely%20offer%20to%20restart%20the%20%E2%80%98Black%20Sea%20Grain%20Deal%E2%80%99%20until%20the%20West%20and%20Ukraine%20de-escalate%20and%20meet%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20demands.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20even%20before%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20plane%20took%20off%2C%20India%20withdrew%20major%20custom%20duties%20on%20agricultural%20products%20of%20US%20origin%20like%20frozen%20turkey%2C%20frozen%20duck%2C%20blueberries%20and%20cranberries%20(of%20the%20fresh%2C%20frozen%2C%20dried%20and%20processed%20varieties)%20among%20other%20things.%20This%20is%20the%20second%20round%20of%20custom%20duty%20reductions%20in%20the%20past%20three%20months.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20could%20very%20well%20be%20that%20the%20move%20was%20crafted%20to%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20Joe%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20gains%20as%2C%20often%2C%20Indian%20consumers%20have%20to%20carry%20the%20burden%20of%20US-India%20friendships.%20US%20presidents%20have%2C%20over%20the%20years%2C%20pressured%20India%20to%20open%20up%20its%20agro-trade%20protections.%20It%20is%20in%20their%20interest%20to%20get%20Indians%20to%20buy%20US-origin%20farm%20goods%20%E2%80%93%20along%20with%20the%20other%20staple%2C%20arms.%20Thus%2C%20agriculturally%20speaking%2C%20India%20did%20give%20the%20US%20president%20a%20red%20carpet%20welcome.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20June%2C%20India%20had%20reduced%20custom%20duties%20on%20US%20agri-commodities%20including%20chickpeas%2C%20lentils%2C%20almonds%2C%20walnuts%20and%20apples.%20This%20allowed%20for%20imports%20to%20flood%20Indian%20markets.%20It%20was%20not%20by%20accident%20that%20the%20June%20G20%20agriculture%20ministers%E2%80%99%20meeting%20was%20held%20within%20days%20of%20this%20announcement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGetting%20back%20to%20G20%20New%20Delhi%2C%20another%20important%20agrarian%20buzz%20was%20the%20launch%20of%20the%20Global%20Biofuel%20Alliance.%20This%20clearly%20seems%20to%20also%20have%20been%20a%20move%20to%20please%20the%20US.%20India%20currently%20battles%20deep%20malnutrition%2C%20hyper%20food%20inflation%20and%20bad%20harvests%2C%20yet%20the%20message%20we%20are%20sending%20to%20the%20world%20and%20its%20own%20farmers%20is%20%E2%80%93%20we%20want%20to%20convert%20arable%20land%20for%20ethanol%20production%20and%20not%20food.%20The%20US%20has%20major%20interest%20in%20biofuel%20and%20the%20boost%20of%20a%20robust%20biofuel%20industry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20we%20simply%20examine%20the%20power%20dynamic%20within%20the%20alliance%2C%20it%20is%20evident%20that%20the%20US%20and%20US-based%20biofuel%20industry%20gets%20the%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%20in%20policy%20decisions%20and%20is%20almost%20setting%20the%20agenda.%20Brazil%20is%20also%20rallying%20to%20the%20US%20because%20it%20is%20a%20major%20producer%20of%20bio-fuel.%20All%20the%20while%2C%20Indian%20policy%20makers%20are%20aptly%20parroting%20US%20policies.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbesindia.com%2Famp%2Farticle%2Flifes%2Fwhy-biofuels-might-not-be-so-green-after-all%2F86377%2F1%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etechnology%20is%20neither%20green%2C%20nor%20more%20beneficial%20for%20the%20Indian%20setting%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Plus%20exporting%20or%20importing%20biofuels%20is%20not%20a%20wise%20step%20for%20our%20economy%20or%20farmers.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fmodi-agriculture-wto-msp-policies-niti-aayog%5C%22%3EIs%20Indian%20Agriculture%20Following%20Two%20Policies%20%E2%80%93%20One%20at%20WTO%20and%20Another%20at%20Home%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20action%20since%20meeting%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20next%20important%20deadlock%20on%20agriculture%20is%20the%20follow%20up%20on%20the%20G20%20agriculture%20ministers%E2%80%99%20meeting.%20The%20outcome%20document%20read%20well%20and%20promoted%20%E2%80%9Cprinciples%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20practical%20solutions%20to%20address%20growing%20food%20security%20and%20agrarian%20issues%20seemed%20not%20to%20be%20in%20focus.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20personally%20said%20at%20the%20G20%20agriculture%20ministers%E2%80%99%20meeting%20that%20%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20G20%20priorities%20in%20agriculture%20focus%20on%20healing%20our%20%E2%80%98One%20Earth%E2%80%99%2C%20creating%20harmony%20within%20our%20%E2%80%98One%20Family%E2%80%99%20and%20giving%20hope%20for%20a%20bright%20%E2%80%98One%20Future%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CTraditional%20practices%20from%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20may%20inspire%20us%20to%20develop%20alternatives%20for%20regenerative%20agriculture%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20even%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CFarmers%20all%20over%20India%20are%20taking%20up%20natural%20farming%20now.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%2C%20no%20steps%20were%20taken%20to%20formalise%20a%20global%20regenerative%20agriculture%20alliance%20in%20the%20final%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration.%20The%20document%20instead%20says%20that%20member%20countries%2C%20%E2%80%9CRecognize%20the%20importance%20of%20sustainable%20biofuels%20in%20our%20zero%20and%20low-emission%20development%20strategies%2C%20and%20note%20the%20setting%20up%20of%20a%20Global%20Biofuels%20Alliance.%E2%80%9D%20Notably%2C%20%E2%80%98agriculture%E2%80%99%20is%20only%20mentioned%20a%20grand%20total%20of%20six%20times%20in%20the%20document%20%E2%80%93%20three%20of%20which%20are%20direct%20mentions%20of%20the%20earlier%20agriculture%20ministers%E2%80%99%20and%20scientists%E2%80%99%20meetings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20clear%20to%20me%20that%20Modi%20wanted%20to%20promote%20industrial%20agriculture%20through%20the%20biofuel%20industry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFarmers%20should%20also%20be%20watchful%20as%20the%20outcome%20document%20put%20India%20on%20the%20path%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdigitalisation%20of%20agriculture%E2%80%9D%20which%20could%20not%20be%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20millions%20of%20farmers%20in%20the%20G20%20nations%20who%20don%E2%80%99t%20even%20own%20a%20smartphone.%20Plus%20they%20offer%20up%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20highest%20number%20of%20farmers%20for%20big%20tech%20grabs.%20This%20policy%20seems%20like%20an%20imposition%2C%20as%20no%20farmers%20were%20involved%20in%20this%20decision.%20If%20not%20for%20a%20forced%20demonetisation%2C%20Indian%20farmers%20would%20not%20have%20accepted%20the%20digital%20payments%20at%20all.%20Digitalisation%20in%20developing%20G20%20countries%20will%20have%20huge%20social%20and%20economic%20costs%20as%20education%20and%20digital%20literacy%20is%20already%20low%20and%20oftentimes%20underprivileged%20groups%20get%20left%20out%20from%20digitalisation%20drives.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERecently%2C%20it%20was%20reported%20that%20the%20leaders%20in%20New%20Delhi%20G20%20were%20talking%20of%20global%20food%20security%20threatened%20by%20growing%20poverty%2C%20climate%20change%2C%20pandemics%20and%20conflicts%2C%20but%20so%20far%20no%20decision%20on%20the%20action%20plan%20has%20come.%20Russian%20food%20and%20agri%20supplies%20may%20ameliorate%20the%20problem%2C%20but%20it%20seems%20they%20were%20blocked%20again.%20G20%20could%20have%20provided%20an%20important%20platform%20for%20food%20aid%20reducing%20world%20hunger%20not%20only%20in%20spirit%20but%20through%20a%20more%20concrete%20step.%20Apart%20from%20Russian%20wheat%2C%20Indian%20farmers%20could%20have%20played%20a%20big%20role%20in%20providing%20for%20nutrition%20needs%20of%20other%20developing%20G20%20nations.%20Other%20countries%20like%20Canada%2C%20Brazil%2C%20and%20perhaps%20Argentina%20could%20have%20pitched%20in%20and%20created%20a%20global%20food%20bank%20or%20reserve%20to%20help%20store%20grain%2C%20stabilise%20prices%20and%20supply%20a%20member%20nation%20when%20in%20need.%20But%20a%20consensus%20was%20not%20reached.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20rumour%20is%20if%20US%20wheat%20production%20increases%2C%20the%20necessity%20of%20Russian%20wheat%20will%20diminish.%20And%20Biden%20could%20offer%20the%20farmers%20a%20huge%20grain%20deal%20to%20keep%20them%20happy.%20So%20another%20geo-political%20battle%20is%20on%20between%20the%20grain%20giants%20over%20filling%20the%20wheat%20vacuum%20in%20the%20international%20markets.%20And%20over%20whether%20India%20could%20receive%20US%20wheat%20instead%20of%20Russian%20wheat%20consignments%2C%20when%20needed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20sum%20it%20up%2C%20the%20G20%20is%20a%20blessing%20for%20US%20agro-traders%2C%20big%20agricultural%20corporations%20and%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20electorate%20base%3B%20what%20it%20does%20for%20curtailing%20global%20hunger%20or%20Indian%20farmers%20is%20hard%20to%20say.%20Without%20a%20global%20consensus%20on%20food%20security%20and%20agrarian%20climate%20distress%2C%20hunger%20around%20the%20world%20will%20only%20grow.%20Once%20developing%20nations%20face%20the%20brunt%20of%20more%20hunger%2C%20diplomatic%20integrity%20and%20G20%20goals%20will%20be%20abandoned%20for%20bilateral%20agreements.%20Promises%20made%20in%20the%20calm%20will%20be%20forgotten%20at%20stormy%20times.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIndra%20Shekhar%20Singh%20is%20an%20independent%20agri-policy%20analyst%20and%20writer.%20He%20was%20the%20former%20director%20of%20policy%20and%20outreach%2C%20NSAI.%20He%20also%20hosts%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Wire%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eagriculture%20talk%20show%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EKrishi%20ki%20baat%2FFarm%20Talks%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20He%20tweets%20%40indrassingh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694417670000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fg20-farmers-agriculture-bio-fuel-india-us%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%E2%80%99s%20personal%20goals%2C%20especially%2C%20seem%20to%20have%20been%20steamrolled%20in%20favour%20of%20US%20policy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Byju's%20makes%20a%20surprise%20%241.2%20billion%20repayment%20proposal%20to%20lenders%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694414604000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-09%2F11%2Ffull%2F1694414512-9722.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fbyju-s-makes-a-surprise-1-2-billion-repayment-proposal-to-lenders-123091100308_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Byju's%20and%20its%20lenders%20have%20been%20mired%20in%20a%20conflict%20for%20almost%20a%20year%2C