C%20does%20not%20look%20like%20an%20eyesore%20on%20the%20beautiful%20hill.%20Instead%2C%20it%20blends%20with%20nature%20and%20actually%20looks%20like%20a%20part%20of%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20philosophy%20of%20the%20couple%20behind%20building%20the%20house%20was%20simple%20%E2%80%94%20they%20wanted%20it%20to%20be%20efficient%2C%20cosy%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F187566%2Fchennai-architect-sustainable-homes-eco-friendly-construction-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eand%20nature-friendly.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20wife%20and%20I%20were%20the%20sole%20designers%20of%20the%20house.%20We%20did%20everything%20from%20scratch.%20We%20wanted%20the%20house%20to%20be%20comfortable%20and%20nature-friendly%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-3-1693576553.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22All%20the%20materials%20used%20in%20the%20house%20are%20sourced%20locally%20to%20improve%20the%20local%20economy%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-3-1693576553.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-3-1693576553-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-3-1693576553-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-3-1693576553-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-3-1693576553-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-328892%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAll%20the%20materials%20used%20in%20the%20house%20are%20sourced%20locally%20contributing%20to%20the%20local%20economy%3B%20Picture%20credit%3A%20Kartik%20Budhraja%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20the%20various%20sustainable%20features%20of%20the%20house%2C%20Kartik%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20studied%20the%20area%20and%20land%20very%20well.%20We%20wanted%20to%20have%20a%20carbon%20negative%2C%20water%20efficient%20and%20climate-resistant%20home.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20the%20materials%20used%20in%20the%20house%20are%20sourced%20locally%20as%20we%20wanted%20to%20contribute%20to%20the%20local%20economy.%20The%20bricks%20used%20in%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20house%20were%20fly%20ash%20bricks.%20We%20used%20them%20as%20they%20have%20a%20lesser%20carbon%20footprint%20and%20are%20more%20energy%20efficient%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20keep%20the%20house%20energy%20efficient%2C%20the%20couple%20installed%20solar%20power%20in%20their%20home.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20an%208%20KW%20solar%20plant%20set%20up%20to%20produce%2072%20to%2080%20percent%20of%20the%20power%20needs%20of%20the%20house.%20Additionally%2C%20we%20also%20have%20a%20rainwater%20harvesting%20plant%20set%20up.%20We%20catch%20about%2030%2C000%20litres%20of%20water%20in%20our%20underground%20water%20storage%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20house%20also%20believes%20in%20zero%20waste%20and%20has%20a%20water%20filtration%20system.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20our%20grey%20water%20(the%20dirty%20but%20reusable%20water%20from%20sinks%2C%20washing%20machines)%20is%20filtered%20and%20is%20used%20in%20cleaning%20and%20drinking.%20Even%20the%20wood%20packaging%20in%20which%20our%20windows%20and%20doors%20came%20were%20used%20to%20make%20some%20sort%20of%20furniture%20so%20that%20nothing%20goes%20to%20waste%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20house%20also%20has%20double%20glazing%20in%20the%20windows%20to%20keep%20it%20warm%20during%20the%20winter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20effort%20to%20combine%20traditional%20and%20contemporary%20elements%20in%20their%20home%2C%20the%20Budhrajas%20acquired%20all%20of%20their%20wood%20from%20a%20%3Cem%3Ekabadiya%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fem%3E(scrap%20dealer)%20who%20sources%20the%20wood%20from%20dismantled%20and%20ageing%20government%20and%20residential%20structures%20in%20Himachal%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20believe%20in%20reusing%20and%20upcycling.%20The%20wood%20in%20some%20of%20our%20doors%20is%20nearly%20100%20years%20old%2C%E2%80%9D%20informs%20Anuradha.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20also%20used%20the%20Himalayan%20Black%20State%2C%20a%20type%20of%20tile%20local%20to%20the%20state%2C%20for%20the%20flooring%20and%20cladding%20of%20the%20house.%20It%20is%20a%20great%20conductor%20of%20heat.%20We%20also%20use%20electrical%20heating%20using%20solar%20power%20to%20keep%20the%20house%20warm%20for%20the%20harsh%20winters%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Anuradha.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCkyB8k4SRwt%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCkyB8k4SRwt%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fd